text: Rush Creek is a stream in Fillmore and Winona counties, in the U.S. state of Minnesota. It is a tributary of the south branch of the Root River. The creek was named for the rush plants lining its banks. ==See also== *List of rivers of Minnesota ==References== Category:Rivers of Fillmore County, Minnesota Category:Rivers of Winona County, Minnesota Category:Rivers of Minnesota
title: Rush Creek (Root River tributary)
